                              <strong>Imagination</strong><br />
                              <i>Poem by Emily A.</i>
                              <br />
                              <br />
                              I went to Hell earlier this week<br />
                              It was not what I was expecting<br />
                              It was a blue grey room<br />
                              Furnished with a couch and a desk<br />
                              Elevator music playing in the background<br />
                              They even had a bowl of those mints you get at
                              banks or at restaurants<br />
                              <br />

                              <img
                                src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/lueeisa/newsforgetterletter/refs/heads/main/rubiks%20cubes.png"
                                alt="Rubix cube unsolved in various block images with rocks and shells placed on to"
                                style="
                                  width: 100%;
                                  max-width: 100%;
                                  height: auto;
                                  display: block;
                                  margin: 0 auto;
                                  border: 0;
                                "
                              />

                              <br />
                              Where was the fire?<br />
                              Where were the melting souls<br />
                              Sizzling in their own agony?<br />
                              Where were the sadistic demons<br />
                              Salivating to torture you for all of eternity<br />
                              With the very things you had been so attached to
                              in your sinful life?<br />
                              <br />
                              Nowhere to be seen.<br />
                              All the things I had imagined Hell to be<br />
                              Were images I made up with my fears<br />
                              Turns out, the world isn’t as merciless as I
                              thought<br />
                              And Hell is just a waiting room<br />
                              And benevolence is the rule<br />
                              And there is very little, perhaps nothing, to fear
                            </div>
